WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.790
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.291 --> 00:14.322
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWS.org.

00:14.342 --> 00:18.908
Today's message comes from Senior Pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.928 --> 00:22.052
Let's open our Bibles to Matthew 25 verse 14.

00:22.072 --> 00:26.257
All right, we are excited about God's Word.

00:26.317 --> 00:27.058
We believe it.

00:27.330 --> 00:30.155
And we want to know how to apply it to our lives.

00:30.195 --> 00:33.060
So this morning, we're going to talk about investing for eternity.

00:33.901 --> 00:34.983
I love a good gift card.

00:35.023 --> 00:38.108
Who doesn't love a good gift card, whether it's to a restaurant or a store.

00:38.529 --> 00:43.437
So I was shocked when I read an article in Forbes magazine.

00:43.918 --> 00:48.626
Forbes magazine says that the average American household has eight

00:48.770 --> 00:57.341
$1,000 in unused gift cards, store credits, and loyalty points over a lifetime, like right now, but over a lifetime, $8,000.

00:57.582 --> 01:00.626
Now, I'm gonna tell you, that's not true at our house.

01:00.646 --> 01:02.108
We use stuff like that.

01:02.228 --> 01:10.879
But that's an amazing statistic to think that that much money just goes unused.

01:11.040 --> 01:16.888
It's not wasted because it's used on bad things, wasted because it's not used on anything.

01:17.729 --> 01:18.770
And Jesus,

01:18.914 --> 01:23.839
is going to tell a story this morning that really relates to something like that.

01:23.960 --> 01:28.645
It is about using what we have to invest in eternity.

01:29.105 --> 01:43.281
And Jesus is going to teach us something in this passage, and that is that failure is not nearly as bad as failing to do something, failing to try, failing to use what you've been given.

01:43.741 --> 01:47.826
You see, all of us have been given gifts from God.

01:48.098 --> 01:50.181
They're not gifts for our own pleasure.

01:50.581 --> 02:06.983
I mean, even though God wants us to enjoy things, they are gifts and stewardships for us to use for his glory and to do good for others, to expand the reach of the gospel to bless the church that Jesus died and rose again to establish.

02:07.444 --> 02:11.710
That's why he gives us these resources and he gives us resources in three ways.

02:12.551 --> 02:13.612
All of us have time.

02:14.874 --> 02:17.778
All of us have talent and all of us have treasure.

02:18.498 --> 02:30.233
And in this parable that Jesus tells, He's going to talk to us about the importance of our investing, our time, talent, and treasure for eternity.

02:30.914 --> 02:34.159
How you spend your life matters.

02:34.900 --> 02:37.143
Now we've been talking about the end times.

02:37.964 --> 02:42.169
And when I come to this parable, first of all, I've preached this parable several times.

02:42.570 --> 02:45.874
I think in the 17 years I've been the pastor here, I've preached it three times.

02:46.466 --> 02:49.990
And I almost said, you know what, I'm not gonna preach that, I've done it before.

02:50.571 --> 02:57.158
But if we really want to learn what Jesus had to say, then I think we need to hear this parable in its context.

02:57.919 --> 03:02.625
And the context is, this is what Jesus started back over in Matthew 24.

03:03.526 --> 03:07.590
When the disciples asked him, Lord, what will be the sign of the end?

03:07.690 --> 03:09.733
And what is the sign of your coming?

03:09.773 --> 03:14.418
And Jesus is saying, this is how you live in light,

03:14.530 --> 03:17.855
of the fact that I am coming back."

03:17.875 --> 03:18.997
And he tells him this story.

03:19.718 --> 03:23.944
So Jesus has talked to us about signs and earthquakes.

03:24.125 --> 03:30.074
And he's talked to us about the rise of a diabolical world leader that we refer to as Antichrist.

03:30.134 --> 03:32.337
And there's this horrible period called the Tribulation.

03:32.637 --> 03:35.141
And then Jesus comes back in his glorious return.

03:35.642 --> 03:38.486
And he says, nobody knows exactly when that's going to happen.

03:38.747 --> 03:40.229
So stop trying to predict it.

03:41.150 --> 03:43.634
But live in a way that honors it.

03:44.258 --> 03:46.101
So Jesus tells this parable.

03:46.221 --> 03:48.063
Now, it's kind of long.

03:49.125 --> 03:53.211
Um, and when I have a long passage, a lot of times I break it up for you.

03:53.231 --> 03:57.717
So we don't just read the whole thing, but I think with a parable, you almost have to hear the whole story.

03:58.238 --> 04:01.903
So I'm going to read the parable beginning at Matthew 24 verse 14.

04:01.943 --> 04:03.766
And then I'm going to talk about it.

04:05.328 --> 04:09.394
Jesus said, for it is just like a man about to go on a journey.

04:09.698 --> 04:15.485
who called his own slaves and entrusted his possessions to them.

04:16.646 --> 04:26.377
To one, he gave five talents to another two and to another one, each according to his own ability, and he went on his journey.

04:27.118 --> 04:33.025
The one who had received five talents immediately went and did business with them and earned five more talents.

04:34.066 --> 04:37.650
In the same way, the one who had received two talents earned two more.

04:38.114 --> 04:45.123
But he who received the one talent went away and dug a hole in the ground and hid his master's money.

04:45.884 --> 04:52.251
Now, after a long time, the master of those slaves came and settled accounts with them.

04:52.812 --> 04:59.440
The one who had received the five talents came up and brought five more talents saying, master, you entrusted five talents to me.

04:59.480 --> 05:01.703
See, I've earned five more talents.

05:02.584 --> 05:03.986
His master said to him,

05:04.642 --> 05:07.626
Well done, good and faithful slave.

05:07.926 --> 05:09.328
You were faithful with a few things.

05:09.669 --> 05:12.032
I will put you in charge of many things.

05:12.753 --> 05:14.795
Enter into the joy of your master."

05:16.077 --> 05:22.486
Also, the one who had received two talents came up and said, master, you entrusted two talents to me.

05:22.986 --> 05:24.909
See, I have earned two more talents.

05:25.550 --> 05:28.914
His master said to him, well done.

05:29.186 --> 05:30.508
Good and faithful slave.

05:30.808 --> 05:32.150
You were faithful with a few things.

05:32.411 --> 05:34.574
I will put you in charge of many things.

05:35.435 --> 05:37.939
Enter into the joy of your master.

05:38.960 --> 05:49.275
Now to the one who had received the one talent also came up and said, Master, I knew you to be a hard man, reaping where you did not sow and gathering where you did not scatter.

05:49.715 --> 05:51.117
And I was afraid.

05:51.838 --> 05:54.863
So I went away and hid your talent in the ground.

05:55.003 --> 05:57.106
See, you still have what is yours.

05:57.858 --> 06:04.407
but his master answered and said to him, you worthless lazy slave.

06:05.308 --> 06:11.316
Did you know what I reap that I reap where I do not sow and gather where I did not scatter seed?

06:11.757 --> 06:16.964
Then you ought to have put my money in the bank and on my arrival, I would have received my money back with interest.

06:17.765 --> 06:27.058
Therefore take the talent away from him and give it to the one who has 10 for to everyone who has more shall be given.

06:27.170 --> 06:40.506
and he will have an abundance but from the one who does not have even what he does have will be taken away and throw the worthless slave into the outer darkness in that place there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.

06:41.948 --> 06:54.162
Now Jesus tells this story and it is in light of the events that he's talked about about coming back again and what Jesus is telling us in this passage is

06:54.690 --> 06:57.172
that we are going to be evaluated someday.

06:57.192 --> 07:03.138
There is going to be a judgment someday and we're going to be evaluated for the way that we use our lives.

07:03.639 --> 07:07.583
So let me give you four truths that come from this parable.

07:07.983 --> 07:08.764
Here's the first one.

07:09.905 --> 07:14.890
Realize that God is the source of every blessing.

07:16.071 --> 07:23.218
Realize that everything you have and everything you are is a gift from God.

07:23.906 --> 07:30.955
When I say gift, however, I don't mean a gift that means it becomes your possession.

07:31.515 --> 07:33.438
It is actually your stewardship.

07:34.038 --> 07:35.781
There's a difference between those two things.

07:35.801 --> 07:39.065
There's a difference between ownership and stewardship.

07:39.766 --> 07:44.431
And all that we are as a gift from God is a stewardship.

07:44.912 --> 07:46.674
God gives it to us.

07:46.818 --> 07:48.380
and we are to manage it.

07:48.440 --> 07:55.811
We are to use it wisely, to bring him great glory and to advance his gospel.

07:56.292 --> 07:57.634
That's why God does that.

07:58.155 --> 08:03.062
If you look at the parable, Jesus says that there's this man and he goes on a journey.

08:03.623 --> 08:05.365
This is a picture of something.

08:05.446 --> 08:07.609
It is a picture of his ascension.

08:07.969 --> 08:16.562
Jesus ascended into heaven and it's like he's been on a long journey, but he entrusted his possessions.

08:16.834 --> 08:17.575
to his servants.

08:18.276 --> 08:23.522
They belong to the master, and he entrusts them to the servants.

08:24.223 --> 08:27.988
Jesus is the master in this parable, we are the servants.

08:28.509 --> 08:34.396
And he has given us these resources that the Bible refers to as talents.

08:35.437 --> 08:39.883
Now, when you hear that, I probably need to bring some clarity to it from understanding the Bible.

08:39.983 --> 08:42.626
The word in the Greek New Testament is the word talaton.

08:43.347 --> 08:45.810
We transliterate it, talent.

08:46.562 --> 08:49.365
And it doesn't just mean some innate ability.

08:50.126 --> 08:59.996
Actually, the word talent on in the Greek New Testament is a unit of measure that was used most of the time for money or finances.

09:00.117 --> 09:04.922
It was used for weighing out gold and silver and any sort of precious metal.

09:05.923 --> 09:12.530
And so he says he gave to one, five talents to one, two talents and to one, he gave one talent.

09:13.122 --> 09:15.965
And that may not sound like a lot, but let me help you with what that is.

09:16.165 --> 09:22.272
A talent was 75 pounds, 75 pounds.

09:23.434 --> 09:27.338
I did the math and I've learned that in the past, I did this incorrectly.

09:28.700 --> 09:31.262
So if you have notes from a previous sermon, let me straighten it out now.

09:31.863 --> 09:36.989
I learned that a Troy ounce by which gold and silver are measured is different from just an ounce.

09:38.090 --> 09:41.554
So if you use Troy ounces for gold

09:41.826 --> 09:46.093
The market price for gold on Friday closed at $2,350.

09:46.173 --> 09:56.290
That means that 75 pounds of gold is $2.6 million.

09:56.711 --> 10:08.530
So to the one, he gave $12 million to another, he gave about $5 million.

10:08.962 --> 10:11.525
and to the one he gave $2.6 million.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.668
Now, this is not a paltry sum.

10:14.728 --> 10:18.271
This is not an insignificant investment that he is making.

10:18.892 --> 10:26.580
He is actually giving adequate resources for these three servants to do something great for him.

10:27.281 --> 10:30.884
You see, the talents are distributed not with equality.

10:30.924 --> 10:36.690
They don't all get the same thing, but they get to each one according to his own ability.

10:38.050 --> 10:41.855
God gives into the lives of His servants.

10:42.596 --> 10:43.497
He gives us time.

10:44.298 --> 10:45.199
He gives us talent.

10:45.860 --> 10:46.801
He gives us treasure.

10:46.821 --> 10:49.966
Now, when I'm using the word talent there, I'm talking about skills and abilities.

10:50.026 --> 10:54.632
God's given you something to use in His kingdom to bring you great glory.

10:55.112 --> 10:59.738
For example, maybe God's given you a natural ability.

11:00.339 --> 11:02.222
Some people can just sing.

11:02.802 --> 11:04.204
They don't need any vocal training.

11:04.224 --> 11:05.586
They can just sing.

11:05.954 --> 11:06.795
Kind of like Sydney.

11:06.975 --> 11:08.176
I mean, it's just amazing, right?

11:08.617 --> 11:09.318
When she sings.

11:10.158 --> 11:11.119
Some people are like me.

11:11.740 --> 11:13.262
They can't play the radio, okay?

11:13.302 --> 11:17.166
I mean, I turn up the radio loud and my wife says, why?

11:17.186 --> 11:19.208
And I say, so I can drown out my singing.

11:19.488 --> 11:23.152
So I sound like Kenny Chesney or George Strait or whoever I'm listening to.

11:23.192 --> 11:29.699
And some people, but some people have this wonderful natural talent that God gave you to sing.

11:31.581 --> 11:32.402
You ought to be using it.

11:33.538 --> 11:36.241
Some people have this wonderful ability to connect.

11:36.701 --> 11:41.747
Some adults have a wonderful ability to connect with students and children.

11:43.388 --> 11:47.513
For some people, it's just a real struggle to make that connection between two generations.

11:47.533 --> 11:49.334
But some people just have this ability to do it.

11:49.675 --> 11:52.097
And it may be it's a natural talent, maybe it's a spiritual gift.

11:52.257 --> 11:52.618
I don't know.

11:54.179 --> 11:54.900
Why aren't you using it?

11:56.402 --> 12:00.466
You see, that's the issue that everything we have is a gift from God.

12:00.962 --> 12:06.027
but it's a gift from God to use in our lives so that we might glorify Him.

12:06.808 --> 12:19.641
James 1 17 says, every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow due to change.

12:20.041 --> 12:22.644
Every good and perfect gift is from God.

12:23.204 --> 12:28.690
Everything you are, everything you have is a gift from His hand,

12:28.802 --> 12:32.227
And not everything that comes to you is meant for you.

12:33.449 --> 12:38.097
That God does want us to enjoy the blessings that He's poured into our life.

12:39.298 --> 12:42.083
But it is not exclusively for me.

12:42.263 --> 12:44.667
God also wants me to bless others.

12:45.488 --> 12:50.416
This past week, I read an article about a lady who won the Virginia Lottery.

12:50.977 --> 12:52.179
And her name is Carrie Edwards.

12:52.239 --> 12:53.160
She's a grandmother.

12:53.240 --> 12:54.322
She's retired.

12:54.690 --> 12:56.993
And now she didn't win like a multi-million dollar thing.

12:57.013 --> 13:01.079
She won $150,000, which that's nothing to sneeze at at my house, okay?

13:01.099 --> 13:02.140
$150,000.

13:02.961 --> 13:09.790
She donated the entire $150,000 to a Navy charity and to dementia research.

13:09.810 --> 13:12.354
Couple of causes that she feels passionately about.

13:12.734 --> 13:17.520
When asked why she didn't keep it, she said, I have plenty.

13:18.101 --> 13:21.746
I have been blessed and I wanted to bless others.

13:22.338 --> 13:25.382
You see, that's what God wants us to do with our time, our talent, and our treasure.

13:25.763 --> 13:29.568
And by the way, if you do win the lottery, remember your church, though I'm not advocating for that.

13:30.810 --> 13:34.595
Though I'm not advocating for that, but playing it, but at any rate.

13:34.615 --> 13:40.243
Number two, faithful stewardship leads to God's best blessings.

13:41.064 --> 13:43.928
Faithful stewardship leads to God's best blessings.

13:44.449 --> 13:51.218
In verse 19, Jesus says, now after a long time, the master came back.

13:51.394 --> 13:59.330
The journey is a picture in this parable of his ascension, then there's this long time, and then Jesus is gonna come back.

14:00.332 --> 14:01.996
So this refers to the return of Christ.

14:02.597 --> 14:08.008
And at the return of Christ, what happens is an evaluation of the three servants.

14:08.870 --> 14:10.994
To the one he gave five talents.

14:11.266 --> 14:12.487
And he earned five more.

14:12.507 --> 14:14.089
He goes out and he does something with it.

14:14.109 --> 14:14.810
He uses it.

14:15.471 --> 14:19.595
The Bible says, Jesus said in the parable that he employs it in business.

14:19.896 --> 14:20.636
Yes, that's right.

14:20.716 --> 14:23.820
You use your business, your job to glorify God.

14:24.901 --> 14:26.242
And he makes five more talents.

14:26.903 --> 14:30.808
And he returns it to the master because it was his anyway.

14:30.828 --> 14:32.409
The next servant's got two talents.

14:32.469 --> 14:33.671
He goes out and does business.

14:33.871 --> 14:34.932
He makes two more talents.

14:34.952 --> 14:35.933
He doubles the money.

14:35.973 --> 14:37.235
What a return on investment.

14:38.916 --> 14:40.338
And he brings those two talents.

14:40.514 --> 14:54.732
Now here's something I want you to notice that in the parable, the one who had five talents and was faithful, the one who had two talents was faithful, they receive exactly the same affirmation.

14:56.034 --> 15:01.321
The issue is not how much you have, it's how you use what you have.

15:01.341 --> 15:05.266
I was reading John MacArthur's commentary on this this week

15:06.114 --> 15:12.801
And he said this, heaven's rewards are not based on prominence or flash, but on faithfulness.

15:13.122 --> 15:17.987
The issue is not what you have, but what you did with what you had.

15:19.629 --> 15:28.238
See, the question for all of us is simply this, am I being faithful with the gifts that God has poured into my life?

15:29.099 --> 15:31.442
God gives all of us the same 24 hours a day.

15:31.842 --> 15:37.309
Am I being faithful with my time or am I frittering away and wasting my time?

15:38.630 --> 15:41.474
Am I using it to invest in my family?

15:41.734 --> 15:44.718
Am I using it to provide for them well?

15:44.758 --> 15:52.587
Am I using it in order to advance the gospel and am I using my time to do good for others?

15:53.308 --> 15:54.189
Those are big questions.

15:55.210 --> 15:56.172
What about my treasure?

15:56.212 --> 15:57.273
Yeah, we're gonna talk about money.

15:57.934 --> 15:59.456
Because the parable is actually about money.

16:00.096 --> 16:01.458
I mean, when you come down to it,

16:02.306 --> 16:07.435
So how am I using the financial blessings that God has poured into my life?

16:08.457 --> 16:09.779
Am I wasteful with it?

16:10.080 --> 16:12.324
Do I spend it on frivolous things?

16:13.246 --> 16:17.193
Now there is nothing wrong with enjoying God's blessings.

16:17.213 --> 16:18.595
Go on a great vacation.

16:19.737 --> 16:21.200
Yes, have a nice home.

16:21.761 --> 16:24.946
It's okay to drive a nice car.

16:25.127 --> 16:26.930
I'm not trying to make anybody feel guilty.

16:27.714 --> 16:30.397
But somewhere in there, there is a balance.

16:30.458 --> 16:42.873
And that balance is between using the gifts that God has poured into my life, that God, that the Bible says that God has given them to us to enjoy.

16:42.914 --> 16:47.119
And somewhere there's a line between that and selfishness.

16:48.341 --> 16:50.643
There's a line between that and self gratification.

16:51.264 --> 16:55.730
And if I'm not using that to help my church advance the gospel,

16:56.226 --> 16:57.528
to bless others.

16:57.648 --> 17:09.006
If I'm not using that so that the gospel will be proclaimed and that others will come to know Jesus in some way, then maybe I need to reevaluate the way I'm using my finances.

17:09.987 --> 17:10.908
What about my talent?

17:12.691 --> 17:14.694
All of you have natural talents.

17:15.215 --> 17:18.861
If you're saved, you have a spiritual gift and you have learned skills.

17:18.881 --> 17:21.965
You went to college or a trade school, you learned how to do something.

17:21.985 --> 17:25.010
Maybe you didn't go to school like that and you just learned stuff.

17:26.050 --> 17:27.411
You have learned skills.

17:28.312 --> 17:31.836
Are you using those to advance the gospel?

17:33.277 --> 17:34.238
See, that's the question.

17:35.319 --> 17:47.812
In 2009, on the show, Britain's Got Talent, a frumpy, overweight 48-year-old woman stepped out onto the stage.

17:49.214 --> 17:52.437
The crowd snickered when she stepped out onto the stage.

17:52.637 --> 17:53.458
There was laughter.

17:55.522 --> 17:56.905
it was this was going to be a train wreck.

17:57.806 --> 18:08.105
Then the judges started talking to her and she was shy and awkward and it just seemed like this was about to go off the rails and she's going to be humiliated and this is going to be terrible.

18:08.787 --> 18:11.011
Then one of the judges said, what are you going to sing?

18:11.051 --> 18:15.419
And she said, I'm going to sing, I dream to dream from Les Mis.

18:16.361 --> 18:19.346
And the judges looked at one another like, that's a

18:19.426 --> 18:22.990
tough song saying, this is not gonna go well.

18:23.010 --> 18:38.124
And then Susan Boyle opened her mouth and the snickering stopped and there was silence as she sang with an almost angelic voice.

18:40.687 --> 18:47.794
But could I tell you that while that was the moment the world learned that she could sing,

18:48.546 --> 18:55.494
The Lord already knew it because since she was nine years old, Susan Boyle had sang in her church choir.

18:57.757 --> 18:59.559
She was using that gift faithfully.

18:59.579 --> 19:04.886
It's just that it showed up on television when she was 48 years old.

19:05.567 --> 19:07.970
She got a recording contract out of that and the whole deal, you know?

19:09.311 --> 19:12.716
Faithful stewardship leads to God's best blessings.

19:12.816 --> 19:18.002
Number three, fear and inaction lead to loss.

19:18.914 --> 19:19.835
Or is that other servant?

19:20.936 --> 19:23.719
And he has been entrusted with one talent.

19:23.919 --> 19:31.468
But remember, while that sounds like not much, I mean, he's got a couple of million dollars worth of resources here to do something with.

19:32.609 --> 19:37.434
But the Bible tells us, and in this story, Jesus says he was fearful.

19:38.335 --> 19:42.900
And because he was so afraid, he buried the gift, and then he blamed the master.

19:43.380 --> 19:44.882
He blamed the master for

19:46.370 --> 19:52.278
for being a hard man and for being demanding and exacting and having high expectations.

19:53.219 --> 19:58.927
The Master says, you should at least put it in the bank in a low-interest savings account that won't make you hardly anything.

19:58.947 --> 20:01.130
At least I've got a little interest back with that.

20:04.054 --> 20:14.629
And so Jesus says the Master takes the one talent from Him, gives it to the one who has ten talents.

20:14.649 --> 20:15.730
That doesn't sound fair.

20:16.706 --> 20:18.008
Where is the fairness in that?

20:18.228 --> 20:18.929
Here's the question.

20:18.989 --> 20:19.931
Where's the grace in that?

20:20.612 --> 20:21.433
I have an answer for that.

20:22.254 --> 20:25.479
Grace never condones irresponsibility.

20:27.142 --> 20:29.445
We are still responsible for our choices.

20:29.485 --> 20:31.629
We are responsible for our actions before God.

20:31.949 --> 20:34.493
We are saved by God's unmerited favor in grace.

20:34.773 --> 20:40.602
But when He gives us a stewardship, a gift into our lives, we are responsible for the way that we use that.

20:41.704 --> 20:43.026
David Jeremiah wrote,

20:43.522 --> 20:47.327
The difference in these three servants is not ability, but attitude.

20:48.008 --> 20:50.872
Two believe the master was worth serving.

20:50.892 --> 20:53.857
One believe the master was not worth the effort.

20:55.198 --> 20:57.041
Just not worth the effort.

20:57.061 --> 21:00.386
You see, fear and inaction lead to loss.

21:00.987 --> 21:05.593
Doing nothing with your life is not neutrality.

21:05.633 --> 21:06.014
Hear me.

21:06.414 --> 21:09.719
It is rebellion against God.

21:11.061 --> 21:11.922
It is rebellion.

21:12.802 --> 21:15.827
when I refused to use what he's given me in my life.

21:16.688 --> 21:23.519
And another one of those singing shows, a cell phone salesman named Paul Potts showed up one day.

21:23.539 --> 21:39.323
He did almost the same thing Susan Boyle did, impressed the judges, but he was a middle-aged guy and someone asked him why he hadn't sung until now and he said this, I lived in fear and hid my gift, but I realized if I didn't use it, it would be wasted forever.

21:40.085 --> 21:40.946
Don't you listen to me.

21:42.562 --> 21:46.929
God has given you something that only you have.

21:48.191 --> 21:55.743
God has given you something to use for His glory, for the good of others to bless people, to advance the gospel.

21:56.103 --> 21:57.645
God has given you something.

21:58.146 --> 22:05.718
And if you don't use it, it will be wasted forever because nobody else has it and nobody else can get it.

22:06.159 --> 22:10.866
It was given to you by the Master and only you can use it in His service.

22:11.906 --> 22:12.627
Fourth and final.

22:15.171 --> 22:19.057
Accountability is inevitable.

22:19.077 --> 22:20.559
The Master is coming back.

22:20.880 --> 22:21.801
His name is Jesus.

22:22.983 --> 22:30.514
And what Jesus describes here in a narrative, in a story, the Apostle Paul gives us in 2 Corinthians 5, 10.

22:31.010 --> 22:43.130
for we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ so that each one may receive what is due for what he has done in the body, whether good or evil.

22:44.151 --> 22:52.064
The judgment seat of Christ is the place where believers will be evaluated, where we'll be judged.

22:53.326 --> 22:58.354
Now I want you to understand that your eternal salvation will not be on the line that day.

22:58.562 --> 23:01.066
That is not what the judgment seat of Christ is about.

23:01.406 --> 23:04.210
The judgment seat of Christ is for believers.

23:05.352 --> 23:14.966
But for those of us who seem to think that how we live doesn't matter, I need you to know that the judgment seat of Christ will be very, very serious.

23:14.986 --> 23:25.522
I also want to bring clarity to something and just briefly, I want to say this because some people have the wrong impression of the judgment seat of Christ and they got it from some tracks from long ago.

23:26.914 --> 23:29.237
The judgment seat of Christ is not gonna go down like this.

23:30.018 --> 23:38.050
Like Jesus has a big screen and he's gonna play back every embarrassing, humiliating sin that you ever committed.

23:38.330 --> 23:39.592
I want you to understand something.

23:40.874 --> 23:45.481
At the cross through his blood, Jesus dealt with your sin.

23:46.763 --> 23:52.992
And God took your sin and he remembers it no more.

23:53.372 --> 23:54.674
That's what the Bible says.

23:54.786 --> 23:58.732
Your sin is not going to be brought up at the judgment seat of Christ.

23:58.992 --> 24:00.875
That was dealt with by the blood of Jesus.

24:02.397 --> 24:10.107
However, how you use this one life he gave you is going to come up.

24:10.128 --> 24:11.529
It is going to come up.

24:11.549 --> 24:14.133
And sometimes our sin does affect the way we use our gifts.

24:14.153 --> 24:15.295
So yeah, that's going to come up.

24:16.236 --> 24:20.362
The consequences of some of our choices probably going to come up.

24:20.382 --> 24:21.343
Your choices matter.

24:22.104 --> 24:23.346
Your life matters.

24:23.618 --> 24:26.080
The way you use what you have matters.

24:26.881 --> 24:34.949
It will matter that day before Jesus because each one will stand before the judgment seat of Christ.

24:35.950 --> 24:39.534
There was a guy named Stephen Covey and he wrote leadership books.

24:40.394 --> 24:46.480
And one of his principles of leadership was very simple, begin with the end in mind.

24:46.681 --> 24:48.482
And here's the way he illustrated that.

24:48.562 --> 24:52.146
He said, I want you to imagine you're at your funeral.

24:52.642 --> 24:53.563
Not a pleasant thought.

24:54.864 --> 24:57.487
But he said, I want you to imagine that funeral.

24:58.528 --> 25:02.232
And I want you to imagine the people who are going to speak at that funeral.

25:03.093 --> 25:04.794
What are they going to say about you?

25:05.956 --> 25:10.520
Now, I would say to you, that's probably a profitable exercise to motivate you in some way.

25:12.142 --> 25:16.747
But when Stephen Covey says begin with the end in mind, what I'm going to tell you is your funeral isn't the end.

25:18.388 --> 25:20.050
It's the only problem with his illustration.

25:21.154 --> 25:24.918
Because the end isn't your funeral.

25:26.320 --> 25:30.304
The end is the judgment seat of Christ for followers of Jesus.

25:33.988 --> 25:35.110
And I want to live my life.

25:36.812 --> 25:40.035
I want to use my time, my treasure and my talent.

25:40.856 --> 25:42.278
And here's what I want to hear.

25:44.180 --> 25:45.181
Well done.

25:46.503 --> 25:49.586
Good and faithful servant.

25:49.858 --> 25:51.741
You were faithful with a few things.

25:52.182 --> 25:53.864
I'm going to entrust you with many things.

25:54.365 --> 25:57.850
Enter into the joy of your master.

26:00.174 --> 26:11.131
See, while we watch for signs of the end of days, Jesus is watching for how we spend our days.

26:16.679 --> 26:18.642
It's not about predicting the end.

26:19.234 --> 26:22.898
I saw it this week, by the way, Jesus was supposed to come back on September 23rd.

26:25.141 --> 26:25.621
He didn't.

26:27.423 --> 26:31.088
What part of no one knows the day or the hour to these people not understand?

26:31.148 --> 26:42.641
But what matters is how you got up on September 24th and used your life to bring glory to God.

26:44.723 --> 26:47.026
If you're a follower of Christ, your life matters.

26:47.586 --> 26:51.892
If you came here today and you are not a follower of Christ though, I won't tell you something, your life matters.

26:52.933 --> 26:58.902
And the choice that you need to make today is to turn from your sin and repentance and give your life to Christ.

27:00.264 --> 27:13.162
Because while the judgment seat of Christ will be intimidating and fearsome and it's going to be very serious, there is a worse place to stand.

27:14.103 --> 27:16.146
The Bible calls it the Great White Throne.

27:17.346 --> 27:27.817
And at the great white throne, if your name is not found written in the book called the Lamb's Book of Life, then you will be cast forever into a horrible place called hell.

27:27.837 --> 27:29.399
And next week, I'm going to preach on that.

27:29.439 --> 27:32.963
